CustomTypes.Name: Access Key State

CustomTypes.Name: Person
CustomTypes.Description: Each user in Halo is defined as a person.

Fields.Name: id
Fields.Description: A unique, system assigned record identifier. The ID format is made up as follows: <cluster-id>:<cluster-position> where cluster-id is the id of the cluster. Halo can have a maximum of 32,767 clusters (2^15-1). The cluster-position is the position of the record inside the cluster. Each cluster can handle up to 9,223,372,036,854,780,000 (2^63) records, namely 9,223,372 Trillion of records!

Fields.Name: name
Fields.Description: The persons real name. e.g. John Doe. Required to create.

Fields.Name: email
Fields.Description: The persons email address. This must be unique. Required to create.

Fields.Name: bio
Fields.Description: An optional person bio.

Fields.Name: company
Fields.Description: An optional company that the person works for or is associated with.

Fields.Name: secret
Fields.Description: The users root credential password. This value is never returned. Required to create.

Fields.Name: status
Fields.Description: The status of the persons account determines whether they can use their account or not. See Person State model for more information.

Fields.Name: createdAt
Fields.Description: A timestamp of when the resource was created. The format is: "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssZ" e.g. "2016-02-14T16:32:47-0500"

Fields.Name: updatedAt
Fields.Description: A timestamp of when the resource was last updated. The format is: "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssZ" e.g. "2016-02-14T16:32:47-0500"

Fields.Name: admin
Fields.Description: A boolean flag designating whether the user is a system administrator.

Fields.Name: username
Fields.Description: A unique username. This name is available system wide for other users to be able to search for collaborators. Required to create.

Fields.Name: guiltyNode
Fields.Description: The node that was responsible or the node that hosts the property that is responsible for the incident generation.

Fields.Name: guiltyProperty
Fields.Description: The optional property that was responsible for the incident generation.

Fields.Name: history
Fields.Description: A collection of historical state changes associated with an incident. See Incident Event for more information.

Fields.Name: details
Fields.Description: Detailed information pertaining to the incident. See Incident Event for more information.

Fields.Name: status
Fields.Description: The current status of the incident. See Incident State for more information.

CustomTypes.Name: Incident State
CustomTypes.Description: A collection of values that can be used to define an incident status.

Fields.Name: GREEN
Fields.Description: Specifies an incident is healthy. This usually denotes that the incident has been resolved.

Fields.Name: YELLOW
Fields.Description: Specifies an incident is recovering . After the cause of an incident is resolved an incident is placed into incubation and is watched until it is considered to be fully recovered.

Fields.Name: RED
Fields.Description: Specifies an incident is unhealthy and the cause of the incident is still active.

CustomTypes.Name: Node
CustomTypes.Description: Nodes are the fundamental hardware devices that make up a sector. They are the physical or virtual devices that make up a hardware distribution network.

Fields.Name: index
Fields.Description: The addressable index of the node in the sector network. This should be in a parent -> child  format with the root/head node first followed by a series of progressive child nodes separated  by '>'. e.g. Root > A Child of 'Root' > B Child of 'A Child of Root'. This index is required to install a node manually.

Fields.Name: name
Fields.Description: The manufacturer specified name of the node. This is normally an extended version of the device acronym specified as the type.

Fields.Name: description
Fields.Description: The manufacturers informational description of the node.

Fields.Name: type
Fields.Description: The manufacturer specified typ of the node. This is normally compact acronym version of the specified name.

Fields.Name: silent
Fields.Description: A flag specifying whether the node should be treated as silent. This flag does not alter any behaviour in the system. It simply propagates its value to incidents that originate from this node. This propagated flag can optionally be included in searches, reporting etc.

Fields.Name: firmware
Fields.Description: The firmware version operating on the node.

Fields.Name: status
Fields.Description: The current status of the node. See the Node State model for more information.

Fields.Name: reachable
Fields.Description: A flag specifying if the node is reachable by Halo.

Fields.Name: installedAt
Fields.Description: A timestamp of when the node was installed or registered in Halo. The format is: "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssZ" e.g. "2016-02-14T16:32:47-0500"

Fields.Name: updatedAt
Fields.Description: A timestamp of when the resource was last updated. The format is: "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssZ" e.g. "2016-02-14T16:32:47-0500"

Halo can have a maximum of 32,767 clusters (2^15-1). The cluster-position is the position of the record inside the cluster. Each cluster can handle up to 9,223,372,036,854,780,000 (2^63) records, namely 9,223,372 Trillion of records!

Fields.Name: extra
Fields.Description: A collection of custom data that can be bound to the node. See the Extra model for more information.

Fields.Name: functions
Fields.Description: A collection of defined functions that apply to this node. This is currently an experimental property. See the Node Function model for more information.
